  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishing a child labour monitoring and remediation system (CLMRS) in Tony&#x2019;s Chocolonely&#x2019;s cocoa supply chain in C&#xF4;te d&apos;Ivoire and Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This projects aims to tackle child labour in the long run by embedding a management information system on the social conditions of farmers in the supply chain. Community Facilitators supervised by Monitoring and Remediation Agents will collect data on the risks and occurrence of child labour on cocoa farms supplying to Tony&#x2019;s Chocolonely. The gathered information will form the bases for addressing the root causes of child labour in cocoa growing communities through remediation activities. This will lead to a reduction of child labour prevalence in the long run. The described approach will be implemented by ICI (International Cocoa Initiative) in close cooperation with the supplying cooperatives in C&#xF4;te d&apos;Ivoire and Ghana.</narrative>
  </description>
